## Key decisions (do not re-litigate without good reason)
- **State scope**: full history log (append-only) + current-state mirror for fast get_state
- **Lua concurrency**: one LState per script goroutine, never shared
- **Script registration**: in-script (ha.on_state_change style), no external manifest
- **KV encoding**: JSON round-trip inside store.state()/global.state() proxy
- **Global KV**: separate global_kv table (not a reserved script_id in script_kv)
- **is_numeric**: set at insert time via strconv.ParseFloat, not re-derived at purge time
- **Timer IDs (every/at)**: stable key = script_id|type|spec|N; INSERT OR IGNORE preserves last_run/next_run across reloads
- **Timer IDs (after)**: UUID per call; row deleted after firing; orphaned rows cleaned up on startup
- **ha.after persistence**: best-effort — survives restart only if called at load time; callback-registered timers are dropped and logged on restart
- **Catch-up semantics**: fire at most once per missed timer (not replay all missed intervals)
- **Scheduler coupling**: scheduler sends TimerFiredEvent via onFire callback → script channel; scheduler does not hold *lua.LFunction references
- **HA add-on**: repo root = add-on directory (single-addon repo); no user-provided HA URL/token (supervisor injects SUPERVISOR_TOKEN + ws://supervisor/core/websocket); scripts at /addon_config/scripts/; DB at /data/ha-lua.db; user options from /data/options.json
- **Config**: production reads /data/options.json; development uses --config flag pointing to config.dev.yaml
- **Lua sandbox**: SkipOpenLibs=true; open base/math/string/table/os/coroutine selectively; nil out load/loadfile/dofile/require/os.execute/os.exit/io/debug/package
- **JSON library**: use github.com/go-json-experiment/json (json/v2) everywhere — deterministic key order, strict UTF-8; import path changes to encoding/json/v2 when it lands in stdlib
- **Lua stdlib modules**: strings (Go strings pkg), time (Go time pkg, userdata with methods), json (go-json-experiment/json v2), re (Go regexp + per-LState cache), http (net/http, uses L.Context() for timeout), crypto (md5/sha1/sha256/sha512/hmac_sha256/hmac_sha512/base64/hex/rand/equal via crypto/* + encoding/*)
- **math augmentation**: add round/clamp/log2/sign to existing math table
- **Tests**: real SQLite (:memory:) everywhere, no mocks; shared helpers in internal/testutil/db.go
- **Benchmark regression**: cmd/bench-check parses benchstat -format=csv output, fails on >10% regression with p<0.05; make test runs this automatically; baseline in benchmarks/baseline.txt (committed)

